    "narrative": "The core of our lineup today revolves around the speed-threat trifecta of **Corbin Carroll**, **James Wood**, and **Jose Caballero**, who anchor the team's pursuit of our scarcest category. **Corbin Carroll** leads the squad with a 71.76 efficiency score, bolstered by a significant 16% park factor advantage and an favorable setup in the two-hole against Triston Rogers. Meanwhile, **James Wood** (67.83) is a priority start at the leadoff spot; his matchup against a righty provides a neutral platoon edge, but the 88% stolen base success rate against the opposing starter\u2019s delivery cadence makes him a primary engine for our category goals. Despite a 19% handicap due to a tough opponent xERA, **Jose Caballero** remains viable in the eight-hole, as the wind-out conditions and a 13% boost from the platoon advantage keep him comfortably above our 50-point threshold.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved the marginal range, specifically the choice to leave **Giancarlo Stanton** (50.28) on the bench in favor of starting **Kyle Karros** (50.40). While **Giancarlo Stanton** offers superior raw power, the optimizer preferred the slight edge in platoon math provided to **Kyle Karros**, despite the latter\u2019s disadvantageous position in the eighth spot. We are also closely monitoring the lineup for **Dalton Rushing** and **Tyler Soderstrom**, both currently subject to \"Lineup Pending\" status; if **Dalton Rushing** is pushed further down the order than our projected seventh spot, his 41.88 efficiency will hover dangerously close to our \"Below Floor\" cutoff, necessitating a potential mid-day substitution. **Josh Naylor** (62.20) and **Trevor Story** (60.10) provide the necessary high-floor stability to round out the active roster, both benefiting from favorable lineup slots and park conditions that mitigate their respective opposing pitcher challenges.",
